text: b'@kryniog The shorter wheelbase only allows for a 75 kWh pack in Model 3 at current cell/module energy densities'
b'@zperrin99 Uses high pressure bleed off the fuel side (RP-1 kerosene) turbopump, so no dedicated pump or fluid needed'
b'RT @TeslaMotors: Supercharger availability is now displayed on your Tesla touchscreen so you can see how many stalls are open before you ar\xe2\x80\xa6'
b'@B0Turner Gravimetric energy density of batteries and achieving a high cell mass fraction'
b'@mcun1 Yes. Green cards & dual citizens already ok. Work & spousal visas not yet, but hopefully soon. This is separate from judicial action.'
b'@dnansink40 Autonomy capability should improve via OTA every 2 to 6 weeks'
b'Validating a GPU driver fix and camera pitch angle health check for HW2'
b'HW2 Autopilot now downloading to all HW2 cars, but in non-actuating mode to assess reliability. If looks good, actuation by end of week.'
b'Mission looks good. Started deploying the 10 Iridium satellites. Rocket is stable on the droneship.'
b'If all looks good, HW2 Autopilot functionality will switch from shadow to active mode by end of week for cars beyond initial 1000'
b'New rev for Autopilot HW2 rolling out Mon to first 1000 & to rest of fleet in shadow mode. Also improves HW1 and enables Ludicrous+.'
b'HW2 Autopilot software uploading to 1000 cars this eve. Will then hold to verify no field issues and upload to rest of fleet next week.'
b'Tesla Autopilot vision neural net now working well. Just need to get a lot of road time to validate in a wide range of environments.'
b'@CJDSB @TeslaMotors About 3 weeks'
b'RT @TeslaMotors: This island in American Samoa now runs on nearly 100% solar energy thanks to 5,300+ solar panels & 60 Tesla Powerpacks htt\xe2\x80\xa6'
b'@vicentes @TeslaMotors @FortuneMagazine big mobile app update coming with 8.1 next month'
b'@BitterMercy Excellent safety in rollover (5 star+). That was what took so long to develop.'
b'@brainwipe There would def be millions of agents simultaneously doing a Monte Carlo sim & combining the results to build a map of weaknesses'
b'Solar glass tiles can also incorporate heating elements, like rear defroster on a car, to clear roof of snow and keep generating energy'
b'Solar roof unveil now at 5:30pm sharp (need daylight, for obvious reasons) California time tomorrow.'
b'RT @solarcity: Thanks to all our customers! It\xe2\x80\x99s been a great couple of months \xe2\x80\x93 we installed more solar than we expected including our 300\xe2\x80\xa6'
b'@TeslaMotors 8 cameras, 12 ultrasonars and radar all flush mounted and body color. Beauty remains.'
b'@vicentes latest autonomous hardware allows for easy computer upgrade'
b'@GoodDayM Something messed up here. Tesla policy is equal pricing for all. No discounts ever unless a car is a floor model or was damaged.'
b'Chamber pressure is almost 3X Merlin, so engine is about the same size for a given area ratio'
b'Production Raptor goal is specific impulse of 382 seconds and thrust of 3 MN (~310 metric tons) at 300 bar'
b'Aiming for Oct 28 unveil in SF Bay Area of new Tesla/SolarCity solar roof with integrated Powerwall 2.0 battery and Tesla charger.'
b'Tesla keeps temp below 40C/105F by automatically venting cabin & turning on AC when needed. Can do this for up to a year on a full charge.'
b'Loss of Falcon vehicle today during propellant fill operation. Originated around upper stage oxygen tank. Cause still unknown. More soon.'
b'@RoadandTrack @TeslaMotors Model Y (compact SUV) off Model 3 chassis. Tesla Bus/Minibus/Spacebus off Model X.'
b'Should mention that Gigafactory will be fully powered by clean energy when complete & include battery recycling'
b'Our radar is using a wavelength of 3.9mm. A good size for both decent resolution and rain penetration. Am hopeful...'
b'@bolayer @SwiftOnSecurity US is ~11 deaths per billion miles. WW is 17 deaths per billion. Autopilot already much better than either so far.'
b'Landing video will be posted when we gain access to cameras on the droneship later today. Maybe hardest impact to date. Droneship still ok.'
b'Upgrades underway to enable rocket to compensate for a thrust shortfall on one of the three landing engines. Probably get there end of year.'
b'Ascent phase & satellites look good, but booster rocket had a RUD on droneship'
b'Creating a neural lace is the thing that really matters for humanity to achieve symbiosis with machines'
b'Crush core is aluminum honeycomb for energy absorption in the telescoping actuator. Easy to replace (if Falcon makes it back to port).'
b'Rocket landing speed was close to design max & used up contingency crush core, hence back & forth motion. Prob ok, but some risk of tipping.'
b'@joshuapinter @juliusvolz Full height of Falcon 9 boost stage on legs is ~165 ft'
b'Most recent rocket took max damage, due to v high entry velocity. Will be our life leader for ground tests to confirm others are good.'
b'@lukealization Max is just 3X Merlin thrust and min is ~40% of 1 Merlin. Two outer engines shut off before the center does.'
b'May need to increase size of rocket storage hangar'
b'Activate autopilot 4X in quick succession for psychedelic cowbell road. And, yes, we are adding more cowbell soon.'
b'@torvos torque is shifted between front & rear motors every ~.01 secs. Traction control is way better than a normal AWD. Digital vs analog.'
b'Model 3 will be RWD, with dual motor AWD optional. Even RWD will have great traction on ice due to fast torque response of Tesla drivetrain.'
b'@CmaxVs Only way to get enough rear passenger headroom was to move the rear roof cross-car support beam. A bike will still fit no problem.'
b'@RGspan Our production ramp plan should enable large numbers of non X/S customers to receive the credit.'
b'@Jbourquee Giga is designed to self-power via solar panels (primarily), wind & geo, using its own batteries to store electricity at night.'
b'Model 3 orders at 180,000 in 24 hours. Selling price w avg option mix prob $42k, so ~$7.5B in a day. Future of electric cars looking bright!'
b'@SpaceX Launch aborted on low thrust alarm. Rising oxygen temps due to hold for boat and helium bubble triggered alarm.'
b'@skiesforme Heavy use of the white causes splitting. Adding backing material to strengthen. Will be upgraded at no cost.'
b'Global economy of $100T is overwhelmingly fossil fuel based, so IMF estimate of $5T or 5% for carbon subsidy is def right order of magnitude'
b'Model 3 reservations ($1000 down) will be accepted in Tesla stores on March 31 and online April 1'
b'My best guess for 2016: ~70% landing success rate (so still a few more RUDs to go), then hopefully improving to ~90% in 2017'
b'If speed at stage separation > ~6000 km/hr. With a ship, no need to zero out lateral velocity, so can stage at up to ~9000 km/h.'
b'Ship landings are not needed for flexibility or to save fuel costs. Just not physically possible to return to launch site'
b'Tap your phone or key and your car will open the garage door, exit, close the door and come to you. Will do same in reverse for unsummon.'
b'First baby step in Tesla Summon capability now downloading over-the-air with V7.1'
b'Static fire test looks good. Pending data review, will aim to launch Sunday.'
b'Aborted on ignition timing due to slow ground side valve. Adjusting ignition sequence by 0.6 secs for next attempt.'
b'Abort triggered by flight computer on upper stage throttle valve. Adjusting thresholds and restarting count at T-10 mins.'
b'5 mins from static fire test'
b'Falcon 9 is vertical on the launch pad at Cape Canaveral. Working towards static fire. Deep cryo liquid oxygen presenting some challenges.'
b'Model 3 is due in ~2 yrs. A China factory for local demand cd be as soon as a year after. A factory in Europe wd happen for same reason.'
b'Autopilot 1.01 coming soon: curve speed adaption, controller smoothness, better lane holding on poor roads, improved fleet learning!'
b'Autopilot release to Europe and Asia pending regulatory approval. Hopefully get the ok in the next few weeks.'
b'CH4 rapidly decays back to CO2 & is absorbed by plants. What matters is adding new carbon to surface cycle from underground oil, gas & coal.'
b'@Avron_p you can mount a rack to the roof via suction cups and still have one Falcon door work fine. Guaranteed up to 140 mph.'
b'Model 3, our smaller and lower cost sedan will start production in about 2 years. Fully operational Gigafactory needed.'
b'With same options, Model X is $5k more than an S due to greater size & body complexity. Sig Series is fully loaded, hence high price.'
b'Max acceleration was 6X gravity, altitude 1187m, lateral distance 1202m and velocity 155 m/s. Main chutes deployed 970m.'
b'Rocket launch good, satellite in geo transfer orbit. Still so damn intense. Looking fwd to it feeling normal one day.'
b'@bonnienorman New Roadster battery should complete safety validation by end of July, so likely available in August'
b'Droneship is fine. No hull breach and repairs are minor. Impact overpressure is closer to a fast fire than an explosion.'
b'Ascent successful. Dragon enroute to Space Station. Rocket landed on droneship, but too hard for survival.'
b'3 mins to liftoff'
b'Odds of rocket landing successfully today are still less than 50%. The 80% figure by end of year is only bcs many launches ahead.'
b'Battery "breakthroughs" need to state power *and* energy density (not the same thing), plus how long they last. They usually fail on energy.'
b'SolarCity just hit a new daily energy record of 5GWh two weeks after reaching 4GWh'
b'Flying car pros: travel in 3D fast. Cons: risk of car falling on head much greater, noisy, grounded in bad weather'
b'Battery pack swap is active between SF and LA and seems to be working well. Supercharging is the future, though, for non-commercial traffic.'
b'Upgrades in the works to allow landing for geo missions: thrust +15%, deep cryo oxygen, upper stage tank vol +10%'
b'Both satellites deployed on target. Now firing their ion thrusters to reach geo station over Europe & Asia.'
b'Rocket soft landed in the ocean within 10m of target & nicely vertical! High probability of good droneship landing in non-stormy weather.'
b'Mega storm preventing droneship from remaining on station, so rocket will try to land on water. Survival probability <1%.'
b'Rocket reentry will be much tougher this time around due to deep space mission. Almost 2X force and 4X heat. Plenty of hydraulic fluid tho.'
b'P85 acceleration will also improve, but not quite as much'
b'Tesla dual motor cars are also all-wheel drive. Main goal of dual motor was actually insane traction on snow. Insane speed was a side effect'
b'Next rocket landing on drone ship in 2 to 3 weeks w way more hydraulic fluid. At least it shd explode for a diff reason.'
b'@alankerlin Hydraulics are usually closed, but that adds mass vs short acting open systems. F9 fins only work for 4 mins. We were ~10% off.'
b'Upcoming flight already has 50% more hydraulic fluid, so should have plenty of margin for landing attempt next month.'
b'Ascent phase good. Dragon deployed to Space Station rendezvous orbit.'
b'Roadster upgrade will enable non-stop travel from LA to SF -- almost 400 mile range. Details tmrw. Merry Christmas!'
b'Pack swap now operating in limited beta mode for SF to LA route. Can swap battery faster than visiting a gas station. Tesla blog out soon.'
b'Grid fins are stowed on ascent and then deploy on reentry for "x-wing" style control. Each fin moves independently for pitch/yaw/roll.'
b'Base is 300 ft by 100 ft, with wings that extend width to 170 ft. Will allow refuel & rocket flyback in future.'
b'Also, lease price improvement is due to US Bank deal. It is *not* a discount. Revenue to Tesla is unchanged.'
b'Calendar app w tap to nav & traffic predictor in Tesla V6.0 release will radically improve how the car adapts to the owner over time'
b'Three engine F9R Dev1 vehicle auto-terminated during test flight. No injuries or near injuries. Rockets are tricky \xe2\x80\xa6'
b'Rocket booster reentry, landing burn & leg deploy were good, but lost hull integrity right after splashdown (aka kaboom)'
b'Goal is for unsubsidized solar power to cost less than grid electricity from coal or fracked gas'
b'Orbit insertion and Dragon deploy all good. Falcon reentry burn also good. Waiting for landing data from tracking plane.'
b'This is 1st ever orbital rocket launch w landing legs. Will attempt leg deploy & soft landing out to sea.'
b'Leasing a Model S takes 5 mins online, no signatures & one tap on car center screen to accept when delivered'
b'RT @TeslaMS60: Arrived in #hawthorne completing 7740 mile round trip #coasttocoasttocoast in a @TeslaMotors #modelS60 in 9.5 days. For free.'
b'Tesla Supercharger network now energized from New York to LA, both coast + Texas! Approx 80% of US population covered.'
b'@simonhackett Yes, definitely needs a huge amount of battery capacity. ~1/3 of energy produced during day must be stored'
b'The gas generator is a small rocket engine that powers the turbopump, which produces 7000 horsepower & weighs 160 lbs'
b'Engines are cycling cleanly w ground pneumatics. Replaced gas generator on engine 9 (center) as a precautionary measure.'
b'Rocket engines are healthy, but cleaning turbopump gas generators will take another day. Aiming for Mon eve launch.'
b'Increasing helium spin start pressure. Probably <50% chance of passing all aborts, but worth a try. Countdown resuming ...'
b'Launch aborted by autosequence due to slower than expected thrust ramp. Seems ok on closer inspection. Cycling countdown.'
b'@lomac92 @WIRED No, almost all fuel/ox is being reserved for SES satellite to give max chance of success'
b'Saw pressure fluctuations on Falcon boost stage liquid oxygen tank. Want to be super careful, so pushing launch to Thurs.'
b'Will be toughest mission to date. Requires coast + upper stage restart + going to 80,000 km altitude (~1/4 way to moon).'
b'Rocket booster relit twice (supersonic retro & landing), but spun up due to aero torque, so fuel centrifuged & we flamed out'
b'Approach is 360 deg flush mounted tiny cameras + radar (prob not lidar). Lot of software & hardware level image processing.'
b'Will do another static fire of rocket to make sure all is good & AF needs to test ICBMs, so probable launch Sept 29/30.'
b'@TobiasVdb Yes, it is a purely propulsive landing, but using the huge landing gear A frames as air brakes. Landing prop < 5% of vehicle mass'
b'Just completed full mission duration firing of next gen Falcon 9 booster. V proud of the boost stage team for overcoming many tough issues.'
b'@arthurblake Tesla service can do coating or can be done by any auto glass coating company. My car is done on side & rear'
b'@arthurblake Turn off AC recirc, so that cool air flows out thru rear vents & get IR coating on rear glass.'
b'Battery pack swap works with all Tesla Model S cars, past and present. It was always there.'
b'Battery storage of solar power needed for night operation & to buffer grid during day. Beta projects are going well.'
b'Vac thrust of 700 tons means avg of 14 tons/floor of structural steel for a 50 story building.'
b'@williamricci6 50% higher. ~1.3 M lbs sea level and ~1.5 M lbs vacuum thrust. Will be 60% higher with some tweaks.'
b'Would love to do a pickup truck. Something w ultra low cg for sports car handling, dynamic air suspension & mega torque.'
b'Technically, I "got rich" from Zip2 & PayPal w zero govt anything, then put 100% of that into SpaceX, Tesla & SolarCity.'
b'If consumption is low, then the tax is proportionately low. We should prob not have tax on basic foods & critical meds.'
b'Net of gas savings, a Tesla is $550 to $600/month with down payment taken care of by tax credits. Maybe less costly then it first seems.'
b'Big difference between taxing people and taxing purchases (ie consumption). Much better to emphasize the latter.'
b'Me & other private money funded Tesla for first 7 years, got IPO+ govt money for 3, now paid back. Yes, carbon tax would be a better way.'
b"Weight of scientific evidence. Taxes don't ban a purchase, they just increase cost. Am against bans, except in extreme cases."
b'Exactly. Better to tax known bad thing and incent desired outcome, instead of subsidizing particular solution paths. Let market decide.'
b'@McBartVolgers @SpaceX High pressure helium pneumatic bolts and pistons. No explosives.'
b'Improving service and honing manufacturing efficiency are the biggest short term challenges. Not sales constrained.'
b'Tesla priority is electrification of cars, so priority is Model S, Model X, then mass market third gen vehicle & truck'
b'@BigBalli High pressure helium. Needs to be ultra light. All 4 legs together (~60 ft span) weigh less than Model S.'
b'About to do chocolate egg hunt with all the kids. Candy bonanza! Happy Easter!'
b'Recovery ship has secured Dragon. Powering down all secondary systems. Cargo looks A ok.'
b'Telemetry says main parachutes deployed ... now visually confirmed'
b'Dragon deorbit burn was good. All thrusters operating. On target for splashdown.'
b'But when considering savings of gas v electricity, true cost vs gas cars is more like $25k for a v sweet ride'
b'Orbit raising burn successful. Dragon back on track.'
b'Thruster pods one through four are now operating nominally. Preparing to raise orbit. All systems green.'
b'Attempting bring up of thruster pods 2 and 4'
b'Solar array deployment successful'
b'Thruster pod 3 tank pressure trending positive. Preparing to deploy solar arrays.'
b'Holding on solar array deployment until at least two thruster pods are active'
b'@_ChrisSimmons A carbon tax would affect coal even more than gasoline, so electricity would also become more expensive'
b'Rocket static fire @SpaceX Cape Canaveral launch pad looks good. Engines generated 433 tons of thrust, parameters nominal.'
b'Btw, more free East Coast Superchargers coming soon. Will allow lower initial charge, v high speed trip & long detours, like NYTimes drive.'
b'Doing LA to SF road trip in Model S with all 5 kids & Talulah. Supercharger finished charging b4 we finished our burgers!'
b'RT @TeslaMotors: Tesla Supercharger network opens today. Charge for free in Model S on your next road trip btwn SF and LA, Tahoe & V ...'
b'1st pure solar gigawatt hour day just achieved by @SolarCity! Predict 1st terawatt hour day from all US solar < 15 years.'
b'Goal for Model S is to show that electric is way way better than gas. Combine w solar power & the future looks bright.'
b'Now back to work. Intense months ahead as we ramp production of rockets and cars.'
b'Splashdown successful!! Sending fast boat to Dragon lat/long provided by P3 tracking planes #Dragon'
b'Thrusters will also fire during reentry to adjust touchdown point. Next version will land w helicopter precision #Dragon'
b'Major Tesla milestone: All crash testing is complete for 5* (max) safety rating. Cars can now be built for sale to public!'
b'Simulations show launch ok with bad valve. Still, better to stop & fix. Recalling rockets after launch is not an option.'
b'Launch aborted: slightly high combustion chamber pressure on engine 5. Will adjust limits for countdown in a few days.'
b'Making large scale rocket propulsion landing work well is a critical step towards a fully reusable Mars transport system'
b'Bought some wood and built a little treehouse with my boys. Few more beautiful ways to spend an afternoon.'
